                            <comment id="17477510" author="jira-bot" created="Tue, 18 Jan 2022 01:39:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 36585cf45e0925fb50f6cb469f9bf49cad793369 in logging-log4j2&apos;s branch refs/heads/release-2.x from Carter Kozak&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=logging-log4j2.git;h=36585cf&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=logging-log4j2.git;h=36585cf&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-3345&quot; title=&quot;log4j-jpl must handle parameters as MessageFormat args&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LOG4J2-3345&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LOG4J2-3345&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: log4j-jpl formats messages correctly using MessageFormat (#713)&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="17477512" author="jira-bot" created="Tue, 18 Jan 2022 01:40:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit d5a620b9e2b15cab108665c3908d526353bd6773 in logging-log4j2&apos;s branch refs/heads/master from Carter Kozak&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=logging-log4j2.git;h=d5a620b&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=logging-log4j2.git;h=d5a620b&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-3345&quot; title=&quot;log4j-jpl must handle parameters as MessageFormat args&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LOG4J2-3345&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LOG4J2-3345&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: log4j-jpl formats messages correctly using MessageFormat (#713)&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="17503589" author="spannjp" created="Wed, 9 Mar 2022 13:24:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ckozak&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ckozak&quot;&gt;ckozak&lt;/a&gt;, this is a breaking change for applications developed against System Logger and expecting the curly braces pattern without indices.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17503605" author="ckozak" created="Wed, 9 Mar 2022 14:09:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The System.Logger API that this implements requires MessageFormat formatting, the api is not aware of curly brace placeholders without indices:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.oracle.com/javase/9/docs/api/java/lang/System.Logger.html#log-java.lang.System.Logger.Level-java.lang.String-java.lang.Object...-&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://docs.oracle.com/javase/9/docs/api/java/lang/System.Logger.html#log-java.lang.System.Logger.Level-java.lang.String-java.lang.Object...-&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; format&#160;- the string message format in&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.oracle.com/javase/9/docs/api/java/text/MessageFormat.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;tt&gt;MessageFormat&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#160;format&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Libraries which consume this API cannot make assumptions about what types of formatting will be supported by the underlying logging framework. That would be reasonable if they used log4j-api or slf4j loggers which explicitly support curly brace placeholders, but not System.Logger.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17504312" author="spannjp" created="Thu, 10 Mar 2022 14:40:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ckozak&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ckozak&quot;&gt;ckozak&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I must admit I was not aware of this &quot;fine print&quot; regarding &lt;tt&gt;MessageFormat&lt;/tt&gt; somewhat hidden in the Javadoc. MessageFormat is an unfortunate choice imho.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The behavior of &lt;tt&gt;log4j-jpl&lt;/tt&gt; thus has been wrong since March 2020 when the module was first introduced?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Given its impact maybe this change should have been introduced in a Major not a Minor release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
